# Joo Navigation

Project safety rules beat AI navigation rules. Treat `AI_INDEX.md`, map shards, sidecar file hints, and optional source-header exceptions as hints, not truth.

Read order:

1. user-provided exact files
2. project/team safety rules
3. error log/failing command anchors when present; create a temporary `[FAILURE_TRIAGE]` card before source reads
4. `rules/context-navigation.md`
5. `AI_INDEX.md`
6. at most one relevant `.ai/indexing/maps/*` shard
7. sidecar file hints
8. relevant source files
9. imports from the first relevant source file
10. one companion shard only when a coupling signal exists
11. relevant tests
12. targeted search only if needed

Do not read every map shard. For failures, file/line/test/userland stack anchors beat keyword search and generated files are never first-read files. Hard cap before edit: 2 map shards, 5 source files, then decide or search targeted.

If metadata is stale, source/imports/tests win. Recover with exact lookup/import/test/targeted symbol search and update only affected metadata when maintenance is in scope.

Report only files read, reason, next target, and uncertainty.


## Exact Path Lookup Rule

When the user names an exact source file, open that file first. If the task is not trivial, lookup only that exact path in `.ai/indexing/file-map.candidate.json` or the relevant map shard. Do not read a whole map for one known path.
